Cold weather pushes locusts out of Nyandarua County             Mt Kenya Star  02nd Mar 2020 13:18:57 GMT +0300 Mt Kenya Star  02nd Mar 2020 13:18:57 GMT +0300 Mt Kenya Star   A section of Nyandarua Disaster Management Committee members when the team visited Ndaragwa sub-county after desert locusts were sighted in the area last week. The insects later moved to the neighbouring Laikipia without causing much damage. [David Mugunyu, Standard]   A section of Nyandarua Disaster Management Committee members when the team visited Ndaragwa sub-county after desert locusts were sighted in the area last week. The insects later moved to the neighbouring Laikipia without causing much damage. [David Mugunyu, Standard] A section of Nyandarua Disaster Management Committee members when the team visited Ndaragwa sub-county after desert locusts were sighted in the area last week. The insects later moved to the neighbouring Laikipia without causing much damage. [David Mugunyu, Standard] A section of Nyandarua Disaster Management Committee members when the team visited Ndaragwa sub-county after desert locusts were sighted in the area last week. The insects later moved to the neighbouring Laikipia without causing much damage        Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. Do not miss out on the latest news. Join the Standard Digital Telegram channel HERE. HERE.  #mc_embed_signup{background:#fff; clear:left; font:14px Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; }
